    <Entry>
      <ID>14</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Player Name],

Perhaps your continued and faithful service shall remind the Archons of their duties to the Overlord. One can hope.

May fortune favor your endeavor.

- [url=glossary:tunon]Tunon[/url] the Adjudicator, Archon of Justice</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>15</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Player Name],

The wrath of the Overlord falls heavily upon those who have earned it, and we are but instruments of [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url]' terrible will. Disobedience, incompetence, and betrayal require the harshest possible response, lest the world falter and descend again into anarchy. Forget not who you serve, and know that all you do, you do in the name of order and tranquility.

That name is [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url].

- [url=glossary:tunon]Tunon[/url] the Adjudicator, Archon of Justice</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>16</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Player Name],

I choose to acknowledge the words of your missive and disregard the spirit.

This time.

Consider your tone more carefully in the future. [url=glossary:bleden mark]Bleden Mark[/url] takes particular interest in those agents of the court who presume to write above their station.

- [url=glossary:tunon]Tunon[/url] the Adjudicator, Archon of Justice</DefaultText>
